Vheadline
p2
VEvergreen kritis of Tyagaraja
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe music series began with Ashtapathi bhajans, Divyanama bhajans and  Sita Kalyanam.O.S.Thiagarajan was the first to present a concert at Goratha Corner, Srirangam. With T.V.Ramanujasaryulu on the violin, B. Harikumar on the mridangam and &#8216;Kovai&#8217;  V. Mohanram on the ghatam,  Thiagarajan rendered evergreen kritis of the  saint-musician. Sanjay Subramaniam, Sangeetha Sivakumar and T.M.Krishna filled the evenings with soulful music on the first three days.Sriram Devanathan, V. Debesh and S. Kasthurirangan, accompanied by Tiruvallur V. Parthasarathy on the violin, Salem K. Srinivasan on the mridangam and Vishnupuram Ragu on the morsing, picked up rare kritis with elaborate alapanas.Maharajapuram K. Nagarajan, Nisha Rajagopal, Vijay Siva, T.N.S. Krishna, R. Madhvaprasad and P. Sudharshan gave a melodic treat.Aishwarya Vidhya Ragunath wrapped up the Carnatic series with style. Accompanied by T.H.Vasantha on the violin, R. Mathvaprasad on the mridangam and M. Deenadayalu on the morsing, she belted out kritis with refreshing niraval.
